{
  "texts": [
    "To quantify these interactions, we decomposed the response variance 37 of each model LC unit into four components (Fig. 3e).",
    "Most model LC units encoded changes in female position (Fig. 3e, orange bars), roughly half encoded female size (Fig.",
    "3e, blue bars), and female rotation was weakly encoded (Fig. 3e, green bars are small).",
    "However, almost all model LC units encoded some nonlinear interaction among the three visual parameters (Fig. 3e, black bars; on average around 25% of the response variance for each model LC unit).",
    "We next considered non-naturalistic stimulus sequences, varying one visual parameter at a time (Fig. 3f, dashed lines, and Supplementary Video 2)."
  ]
}